==English==
===Etymology===
Named after the inventor, mathematician [[w:John Venn|John Venn]]

===Noun phrase===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[w:John Venn|Venn]] [[diagram]]''' (''plural'' '''Venn diagrams''')

#{{settheory}} A diagram representing [[set]]s by circles or ellipses (and sometimes also the [[universal set]] as a rectangle enclosing all of these shapes) and indicating the relationships between the sets:
#*by overlapping the shapes to show that the two corresponding sets have a [[non-empty]] [[intersection]];
#*by enclosing one shape entirely within another to show that the first set is a subset of the other;
#*by showing completely separate shapes to show that neither of these facts applies to the corresponding sets

